MYCOPLASMA, CULTIVATION AND ANALYSIS: REQUEST FOR INFO
******************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
Date: Wed, 29 Apr 1998 16:32:19 +0300
From: mserin <serinms@pamuk.cc.cu.edu.tr>

If is there anyone studying on cultivation of mycoplasmas [who] could
answer the following questions, [I would appreciate the information].
1. Is it possible to use horse blood for hemolysis activity of _M.
pneumoniae_?
2. Is is possible to inoculate pre-isolated strains in to glucose [medium]
containing peptone for the fermentation analysis of _M. fermentans_?
